<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. USERS AND COLOMBIAN 'WAR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
University students in Colombia have taken to the streets to protest the 
drug-related violence that has become endemic in their country. An article in 
The Times reported that one of the banners carried by students read, "If You 
Have Consumed Drugs, You Killed (Luis) Galan" (the Colombian presidential 
candidate killed Aug. 18). These words are true for anyone who has ever used 
illicit drugs. 
</P>
<P>
The United States provides the monstrous market for these drugs and therefore 
is directly responsible for the drug-related carnage in Colombia. Every time 
one of us uses cocaine or marijuana, he or she perpetuates this virulent 
market. 
</P>
<P>
SHARON WELBY, Oceanside 
</P>
</TEXT>
