<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. USERS AND COLOMBIAN 'WAR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As indicated in the editorial "Attack on Drug Kings" (Aug. 22), the murder of 
Sen. Luis Carlos Galan has galvanized Colombians into waging all-out war 
against Colombian drug lords. Let's hope they succeed. It won't be easy. 
</P>
<P>
No body of terrorists should be allowed to control the government of Colombia. 
These drug kings must be captured, extradited to the United States and put on 
trial. As mentioned before, this won't be easy, but it can be done if Colombia 
and the United States can work together. 
</P>
<P>
DAN RADEMACHER, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
