DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
PALMDALE MINISTER ROBBED AT CHURCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Palmdale minister was robbed at gunpoint outside of his church, the Los 
Angeles County Sheriff's Department reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Rev. James Griffin was leaving his office at the rear of the First Assembly 
of God shortly after 6 p.m. Saturday when he was confronted by a gunman, Deputy 
Ronald Thomason said. The robber took $15 from Griffin and fled, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The robber was described as a white male in his 20s, Thomason said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
