<P>
MORNING REPORT: ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAUNA SNOW, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Organizers of Save Venice Inc., a U.S.-based group raising money for preserving 
art treasures of the Italian city, say they have raised more than $450,000 to 
finance restoration of the church of Santa Maria dei Miracoli and of lunettes, 
paintings and marbles in three other nearby churches. The money was raised at a 
$1,500-a-person gala last week that ended a four-day festival of private 
parties, concerts and art tours in Venice and nearby Vicenza. Those attending 
the gala included Prince Andrew and his wife Sarah, and Paloma Picasso, 
daughter of the late painter Pablo Picasso. SHAUNA SNOW 
