<TEXT>
<P>
Machine Tool Exports Rise: The United States exported 25.9% more machine tools 
in June than in May, but imports remained high, meaning a continued trade gap 
with other countries, the National Machine Tool Builders Assn. reported. It 
said imports, which are running at three times the level of exports, fell 5.5% 
during that period but were still a solid 24.5% higher than a year ago. In 
June, the United States exported a total of $80.7 million in machine tools, 
compared to $69.1 million in May. 
