<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
WOMAN LOSES CAR, PURSE IN ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anaheim police are looking for two young women in connection with an incident 
in which a third woman was pushed to the ground outside a Disneyland-area 
restaurant, where her car and purse were stolen. 
</P>
<P>
The incident was reported at 6:21 p.m. outside Bob's Big Boy at 1350 S. Harbor 
Blvd. The victim, whose name was not immediately released, was treated at the 
scene by Anaheim Fire Department paramedics but was not seriously hurt. 
</P>
<P>
Police late Sunday had issued a bulletin for the victim's car, described as a 
white Toyota Corolla with California license plate No. 2KOZ874. 
</P>
</TEXT>
